# Deploy the Patched Capture Clients Fleet-Wide

## Step

The patched capture clients are live on flagg, but capture also runs from other machines (failure mode #4, 2026-07-20 grilling): a stale client elsewhere keeps minting cumulative Runs under fresh IDs. The server contains the damage and the growth alert makes it loud, but the fix is not deployed until every capture source runs it. Resolved when:

1. Every machine that runs pi/claude/codex capture (blaine at minimum; verify the actual set from Run metadata `machine_id` values) has pulled the patched clients.
2. Proof by provenance: fresh captures from each machine arrive at flagg carrying `from_offset`/`to_offset`/`jsonl_sha256`/`source_identity`.
3. The machine list and how each was updated is recorded here for the next time.

## Result (2026-07-20)

Run metadata under `~/.joelclaw/runs-dev` contains four `machine_id` values: `flagg`, `blaine`, `panda`, and historical `dark-wizard`. The live Tailscale check showed `flagg`, `blaine`, and `panda` online. `dark-wizard` has no current Tailscale peer and `tailscale debug resolve dark-wizard` returned `no such host`; its newest Run is from 2026-05 and it is not a deployable capture source.

| Host / `machine_id` | Reachable | Pulled to | Capture-client update | Provenance proof at flagg |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `flagg` | yes; local host `flagg` | `c0299e6b77487aacc921b0f94d932988013ebc67` | Already ran the patched checkout. The Pi extension and Claude/Codex helpers resolve to repo files containing the four provenance fields. | Run `ebea40471c3d47779bb3843264`: Pi capture with `from_offset=431788`, `to_offset=434963`, SHA-256 `5dd9d10…`, and `source_identity=sha256:3cd8a42…`. |
| `blaine` | yes; SSH host reports `Dark-Tower` | `c0299e6b77487aacc921b0f94d932988013ebc67` via `git pull --ff-only` | Pi extension is repo-symlinked; Claude and active Codex hooks invoke repo scripts. Reinstalled the standalone Codex helper from the same script; SHA-256 matches `03bb9f9a…`. Repo remained clean. | Canary Run `c8f7b37bcdc347228c5519ea49`: `from_offset=0`, `to_offset=1717`, SHA-256 `785f3a11…`, `source_identity=sha256:6bd42718…`. |
| `panda` | yes; SSH host reports `panda` | `c0299e6b77487aacc921b0f94d932988013ebc67` via `git pull --ff-only` | Pi extension and Claude helper are repo-symlinked. Reinstalled the copied Codex helper; SHA-256 matches repo `03bb9f9a…`. Repo remained clean. | Canary Run `6b17c371fc2f42b28ee2b4e520`: `from_offset=0`, `to_offset=1492`, SHA-256 `f4bc9d9b…`, `source_identity=sha256:5d79463a…`. |
| historical `dark-wizard` | no current machine | not applicable | Historical metadata identity only. No current peer or resolvable host exists. | Gap is retired, not an unverified reachable source. No command can target this removed host. |

All reachable capture sources now run the patched clients, and each produced a fresh capture with the complete provenance field set.
